The '''sociable weaver''' ('''''Philetairus socius''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the [[Ploceidae|weaver family]], endemic to [[Southern Africa]].<ref name="covas">{{cite thesis|last= Covas|first= R.|title= Life-history Evolution and Cooperative Breeding in the Sociable Weaver|type= PhD|year= 2002|publisher= Percy Fitzpatrick Institute - University of Cape Town|url= http://www.cea.uevora.pt/umc/pdfs/tese_Rita.pdf|access-date= 18 January 2011}}</ref> It is the [[Monotypic taxon|only species]] in its genus '''''Philetairus'''''. It is found in South Africa, Namibia, and Botswana,<ref name="iucn status 11 November 2021" /> but its range is centered within the [[Northern Cape|Northern Cape Province]] of South Africa.<ref name="mendelsohn">{{cite book|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061015081716/http://web.uct.ac.za/depts/stats/adu/pdf/800.pdf|archive-date=2006-10-15|last1= Mendelsohn|first1= J.M.|title= The Atlas of Southern African Birds|year= 1997|publisher= BirdLife South Africa|chapter-url= http://web.uct.ac.za/depts/stats/adu/pdf/800.pdf|last2= Anderson|first2= M.D.|editor= J.A. Harrison|editor2= D.G. Allan|editor3= L.G. Underhill|editor4= M. Herremans|editor5= A.J. Tree|editor6= V. Parker|editor7= C.J. Brown|location= Johannesburg|pages= 534–535|chapter= Sociable Weaver ''Philetairus socius''}}</ref> The species builds large, compound, community [[Bird nest|nests]], a rarity among birds. These nests are perhaps the most spectacular structure built by any bird.<ref name="auk">{{cite journal|last1= Collias|first1= Nicholas E|first2= Elsie C.|last2= Collias|title= Weaverbird nest aggregation and evolution of the compound nest|journal= The Auk|date= January 1977|volume= 94|pages= 50–64|url= https://sora.unm.edu/sites/default/files/journals/auk/v094n01/p0050-p0064.pdf|access-date= 18 January 2011}}</ref>

== Taxonomy and systematics ==
The sociable weaver was first described by ornithologist [[John Latham (ornithologist)|John Latham]] in 1790. Alternative names include the '''common social weaver''', '''common social-weaver''', and '''social weaver'''.<ref name=eol-common>{{cite encyclopedia|title= Common names for Sociable Weaver (''Philetairus socius'')|encyclopedia= Encyclopedia of Life|url = http://eol.org/pages/919094/names/common_names |access-date= 28 March 2014}}</ref> Formerly, four subspecies were recognised, but the species is now considered monotypic. The sociable weaver is the only extant species in the genus ''Philetairus''.<ref name="itis">{{cite web |title= ITIS Standard Report Page: ''Philetairus''|url= https://www.itis.gov/servlet/SingleRpt/SingleRpt?search_topic=TSN&search_value=558047|work= Integrated Taxonomic Information System|access-date= 28 March 2014}}</ref>

=== Phylogeny ===
